# =============================================================================
# Unhold — Vercel Environment Variables  (Production)
# =============================================================================
# HOW TO ADD: Vercel Dashboard → your Project → Settings → Environment Variables.
#   - Easiest: click "Import .env" / paste, then select Environment = Production
#     (also tick Preview if you want preview deploys to work).
#   - Or add each KEY/VALUE below one at a time.
# Lines starting with # are comments — Vercel ignores them on import.
#
# SECURITY: these are LIVE secrets. After wiring Vercel, ROTATE the database
# password, the SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY, the NVIDIA keys, and the Upstash
# token — they were shared in chat. Update Vercel + .env.local together when you do.
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_* values are exposed to the browser by design (safe to be public).
# Everything else is server-only — keep secret; never prefix them with NEXT_PUBLIC_.
# =============================================================================

